text.__SUMMARY__: Conus miamiensis is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.This species is the type taxon of the fossil genus † Tequestaconus Petuch & Drolshagen, 2015
text.Description: The shell attains a length of 32 mm.
text.Distribution: This fossil species is known from the Plio-Pleistocene of Florida.
text.References:
E.J. Petuch (1986), The Pliocene Reefs of Miami: Their Geomorphological Significance in the Evolution of the Atlantic Coastal Ridge, Southeastern Florida, U.S.A.; Journal of Coastal Research Vol. 2, No. 4 (Autumn, 1986), pp. 391-408
